    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-18T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-18T14:00:00-05:00" n="638"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115A European War/9–844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-18T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 18, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1866. Last paragraph your 3700, September 16, 5 p.m. not clear. Do you mean (<hi
                        rend="italic">a</hi>) that Sweden will immediately release one American
                    airman for each German arriving on a Finnish vessel even though the German will
                    be interned for the duration or (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) that one American
                    airman will be released for each German arriving in this manner who will be
                    offered the choice of remaining in Sweden or returning to Germany?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
